21/11/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The ruling party PASOK presented on Thursday (20 November) its policy orientation framework for the period 2004-2008. 
Prime Minister Costas Simitis stressed that the focus would be on securing public prosperity, convergence with Europe and resolving major domestic issues. 
Greece holds general elections in the spring.
In other news, BTA, citing the Greek radio station Flash, reported on Friday that the country is preparing a military umbrella over Athens and the other Olympic sites to ensure security during the Summer Games next year. 
The project includes round-the-clock patrols by military aircraft over the Aegean Sea, early warning flights by NATO planes and deployment of Patriot missile batteries. 
(BTA - 21/11/03; ANA, MPA - 20/11/03)
